      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PORTARLINGTON (1) was a good in restricted room here fresh then chased gamely into the placings when well supported in the G3 David Coles Stakes on the main track. Peaking now and will find this much easier. Is the one to beat. TWEETER (7) did a good job to place on debut at Gawler and is open to natural improvement with Hutchinson taking over. Can progress but will need to take a big leap to get the verdict. WATERORTHECAN (3) is a Headwater gelding on debut from the sharp juvenile stable of R & C Jolly. Has come along nicely at the trials and is among the minor chances. BREWSTER BUCK (2) next best.",
